cURL Command:
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/customer/login -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"username":"testuser","password":"testpass"}' -c /tmp/cookies.txt

Output:
User successfully logged in

Note: The login creates a JWT access token and stores it in the session along with the username.
The session cookie (connect.sid) is saved to cookies.txt for use in authenticated requests.
